Hikma, Irish Life, Tullow Oil: U.K., Irish Equity Market Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-03-16T07:47:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/hikma-irish-life-tullow-oil-u-k-irish-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in U.K.
and Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices
are from the last market close.  The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index (UKX)  retreated 79.96 points, or 1.4
percent, to 5,695.28. The  FTSE All-Share Index (ASX)  fell 1.5 percent
while Ireland’s ISEQ Index dropped 2.6 percent.    Associated British Foods Plc (ABF)  : Credit Suisse Group
AG raised its recommendation for the U.K. sugar producer to
“outperform” from “neutral.” The shares lost 0.4 percent to
940 pence.    Carillion Plc (CLLN)  : Credit Suisse also upgraded the
building manager for companies including BT Group Plc to
“outperform” from “neutral.” The shares slid 0.6 percent to
361 pence.    Hikma Pharmaceuticals Plc (HIK)  : The Jordanian drugmaker
listed in London reported a 27 percent rise in profit
attributable to shareholders to $98.8 million. The stock
declined 2.4 percent to 703 pence.    Irish Life  & Permanent Plc (IPM ID): Ireland’s biggest life
insurer said its purchase of deposits and government-guaranteed
bonds from Irish Nationwide Building Society last month may have
a “marginally negative” impact on earnings and capital. The
shares plunged 14 percent to 67 euro cents.    Mitchells & Butlers Plc (MAB)  : The pub owner said Chief
Executive Adam Fowle will leave the company and a successor will
be announced in due course. The shares fell 0.6 percent to 299.5
pence.    Tullow Oil Plc (TLW)  : The U.K. explorer with the most
licenses in  Africa  signed a memorandum of understanding with the
Ugandan government over the tax dispute with Heritage Oil Plc
that will allow it to continue oil exploration and development
in the Lake Albert basin. The stock retreated 1.5 percent to
1,349 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
